Anonymous Wed 18 Jan 2023 04:05:49 No.53793543 Report

>>53792998
Oh yes.

The creator of these creatures--apparently it was for an RPG--did an enormous amount of worldbuildan, but also keeps on doing constant retcons to the point where it's impossible to know what's canon this week. I know there were multiple sapient species in this world she called Vilous:

Agudners: humanoid goat people, different artists draw them wildly differently, sometimes they're kemonomimi with a couple of subtle goat features, sometimes they're full on deer and goat furries

Nevreans: smol bird/velociraptor anthros, the males are tiny and effeminate and brightly colored flamboyant and guard the eggs and rear the kids, the females are dull dark colors and are aggressive risk-takers and a bit butch, By far the smol-est of the Vilous intelligent species, they are born engineers who love tools, machines, tech of every kind, and, especially, weapons.

Sergals: shark wolf things that may or may not be mammals this week

Only the sergals get porn. Oh, the world has a few other sapient species, that are VERY alien. No one cares about anything but fucking a sergal, it seems.

Last time I could be bothered to look it up, Deepest Lore was that there was a dying species of ridiculously powerful aliens on this horrifying death-world where evolution took some VERY different turns and most land animals are venomous armored mollusks, often but not always with arthropod type legs--seriously, this world is like something Junji Ito and Charles Stross would have come up with on a cocaine and tequila bender after binging everything Lovecraft wrote. One of these godlike aliens used his l33t magical h4x reality-warping bullshit powers to bring a bunch of humans to the planet, and in the process magically transformed them into these three species to inhabit different horrific biomes on the planet, as some kind of experiment. All these species have supposedly not forgotten that their ancestors were human, though they regressed to Stone Age levels.

>>53793804
If anyone cared, http://www.vilous.net/wiki/Agudners This is the official page, and even the official art shows some of them as being basically human with kemono ears, and some of them are full on goat, alpaca, and cow furries.

I get the impression the author doesn't know quite what to do with the concept. They're supposedly the closest to humans, psychologically. All three species are the only bifurcated, bilaterally symmetrical bipeds with two eyes and a vertically hinged lower jaw on the planet. They don't look much alike until you compare them to any of the native life forms, which could all pass for random weird shit from the Cambrian Explosion.

Agudners are generally peaceful farmer types,and are the ones who practice agriculture and domesticated such of the local animals so far as was possible. Male Nevreans will shriek and run away from danger. Female Nevreans will shank a motherfucker in the face, but they'd really prefer to use this really neat gun they built. Sergals are very intuitive problem-solvers but not great at formal abstract reasoning. Their fight-or-flight reaction is biased more towards flight than a human's, generally, unless they're in a war-band led by someone charismatic, in which case they really love great big axes and other polearms. They are berserkers and melee combat killing machines against which very little in-setting can stand. Nevreans are Scout, Sergals are Heavy Weapons Guy, and Agudners would rather be playing Candy Crush.

Anonymous Wed 18 Jan 2023 07:42:49 No.53797425 Report

>>53797132
There was a "trade center" a couple towns over from me that closed in 2014. It got demolished and now the site has one of those discount club stores. But that image looks very much like a scene from within it. It was this enormous old warehouse and there were dozens of little tiny stores inside it. You could walk around and see a while-u-wait cell phone repair stall, a tattoo place, several head shops, a pet store, computer repair places, toy stores, stores selling airsoft gear, comic book shops, people selling used office furniture and new "carpet remnants," tools, shoes, clothing, kitchen gadgets, used books, old vinyl records. There was a food court that had everything from fried chicken to pizza to hand dipped milkshakes and ice cream.

There was one tiny kiosk that had a machine that made miniature donuts by an automated process, to order, while you watched--there was a hopper full of batter, and the counter guy would press a button and it'd bloop a dozen perfect tiny rings of batter into the fryer, where they'd solidify and brown as it went through a shiny stainless steel conveyor belt inside the deep fryer, then it'd flip them into a pan when they were done and the counter guy would sprinkle them with powdered sugar and give them to you in a bag, still hot. They were the most unhealthy thing in the world, but I would sometimes go there on Saturday afternoons if I wasn't working. And sometimes I'd buy a bag of tiny donuts. It's easy to imagine Avril there behind the counter in one of the toy places. I wish it were still there. I haven't been to the building that was constructed on the old site--it's one of those places where you have to have a membership card. And it's one of a chain, so it's probably boring anyway.
